SIMPLE: counter_tenor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Counter tenor
<hw>Coun"ter ten`or</hw> <pr>(t?n`?r)</pr>. <ety>[OF.
<ets>contreteneur</ets>. Cf. <er>Contratenor</er>, and see
<er>Tenor</er> a part in music.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>One of the
middle parts in music, between the tenor and the treble; high
tenor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Counter-tenor clef</b></col> <fld>(Mus.)</fld>, <cd>the C
clef when placed on the third line; -- also called <altname>alto
clef</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Counterterm</ent>⟦br⟧
